<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0501 </DOCNO><TEXT>Recent progress in the efficient use of air as a heat transfer fluid insolar thermal systems has led to the development of two novel solar appliancesfor developing countries: a cooker and a medical sterilizer. The basicfeatures of these machines are described, as well as a comparison betweenexperiment and thermal simulation calculations. These machines are nowcommercially available. Experiences in different countries are reported.</TEXT></DOC>